usdPPPoEMIB.name: usdPPPoEMIB

revisions.description: Added AC-NAME and duplicate MAC address indicator objects.

Deprecated profile support, which is now in a separate module. Made corrections to MOTM and URL ranges (should allow zero length) and to read-write objects that should be read-create because they are in tables that permit row creation. Fixed upper bound of usdPPPoEIfMaxNumSessions. Fixed conformance definitions.
Added interface summary statistics under usdPPPoESummary node.
Added profile support and new sub-interface objects.
Initial version of this MIB module.

usdPPPoEMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 Email: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdPPPoEMIB.description: The Point-to-Point Protocol over Ethernet (PPPoE) MIB for the Juniper edge router enterprise.

usdPPPoENextIfIndex.name: usdPPPoENextIfIndex
usdPPPoENextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdPPPoEIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdPPPoEIfTable.name: usdPPPoEIfTable
usdPPPoEIfTable.reference: RFC 2156 A method for transmitting PPP over Ethernet
usdPPPoEIfTable.description: The parameters for the PPPoE service on this interface.

usdPPPoEIfEntry.name: usdPPPoEIfEntry
usdPPPoEIfEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular PPPoE interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created/deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable, and usdPPPoEIfStatsTable.

usdPPPoEIfIfIndex.name: usdPPPoEIfIfIndex
usdPPPoEIfIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEntry.

usdPPPoEIfMaxNumSessions.name: usdPPPoEIfMaxNumSessions
usdPPPoEIfMaxNumSessions.description: The number of sessions allowed on the PPPoE interface, zero indicates unlimited.

usdPPPoEIfRowStatus.name: usdPPPoEIfRowStatus
usdPPPoEIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdPPPoEIfRowStatus usdPPPoEIfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdPPPoEIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdPPPoENextIfIndex. The interface identified by usdPPPoEIfLowerIfIndex must exist, and must be an interface type that permits layering of PPPoE above it. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating or destroying an entry in this table.

usdPPPoEIfLowerIfIndex.name: usdPPPoEIfLowerIfIndex
usdPPPoEIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this PPPoE interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdPPPoEIfAcName.name: usdPPPoEIfAcName
usdPPPoEIfAcName.description: The name to use for the AC-NAME tag that is sent in any PADO that is sent on this interface.

usdPPPoEIfDupProtect.name: usdPPPoEIfDupProtect
usdPPPoEIfDupProtect.description: Flag to allow duplicate MAC addresses.

usdPPPoEIfPADIFlag.name: usdPPPoEIfPADIFlag
usdPPPoEIfPADIFlag.description: This flag controls whether always repsond to a PADI with a PADO regardless of the ability to create the session and allows the session establish phase to resolve it.

usdPPPoEIfAutoconfig.name: usdPPPoEIfAutoconfig
usdPPPoEIfAutoconfig.description: This flags determines whether the upper PPPoE interface is created dynamically or statically. When enable(1) the interface is created dynamically.

usdPPPoEIfStatsTable.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsTable
usdPPPoEIfStatsTable.description: The statistics for the PPP over Ethernet Interface for the PPPoE service on this interface.

usdPPPoEIfStatsEntry.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsEntry
usdPPPoEIfStatsEntry.description: The statistics for a particular PPPoE Interface.

usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvVersion.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvVersion
usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvVersion.description: Number of packets received with invalid version.

usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvCode.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvCode
usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvCode.description: Number of packets received with invalid code.

usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvTags.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvTags
usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvTags.description: Number of packets received with invalid tags.

usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvSession.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvSession
usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvSession.description: Number of packets received with invalid session identifiers.

usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvTypes.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvTypes
usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInvTypes.description: Number of packets received with invalid types.

usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInsufficientResources.name: usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInsufficientResources
usdPPPoEIfStatsRxInsufficientResources.description: Number of session requests that could not be honored due to invalid resources.

usdPPPoESubIfNextIfIndex.name: usdPPPoESubIfNextIfIndex
usdPPPoESubIfNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in usdPPPoESubIfTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

usdPPPoESubIfTable.name: usdPPPoESubIfTable
usdPPPoESubIfTable.description: This table contains entries for PPPoE Subinterfaces present in the system.

usdPPPoESubIfEntry.name: usdPPPoESubIfEntry
usdPPPoESubIfEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPPoE Subinterface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created /deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable.

usdPPPoESubIfIndex.name: usdPPPoESubIfIndex
usdPPPoESubIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the PPPoE Subinterface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading usdPPPoESubNextIfIndex.

usdPPPoESubIfRowStatus.name: usdPPPoESubIfRowStatus
usdPPPoESubIfRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: usdPPPoESubIfRowStatus usdPPPoESubIfLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for usdPPPoESubIfIndex must have been determined previously, by reading usdPPPoESubIfNextIfIndex. The interface identified by usdPPPoESubIfLowerIfIndex must exist, and must be a PPPoE interface. A positive value configured for usdPPPoESubIfId must not already be assigned to another subinterface layered onto the same underlying PPPoE interface. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/usdIfTable is created or destroyed as a result of creating or destroying an entry in this table.

usdPPPoESubIfLowerIfIndex.name: usdPPPoESubIfLowerIfIndex
usdPPPoESubIfLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of a PPPoE interface over which this PPPoE Subinterface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

usdPPPoESubIfId.name: usdPPPoESubIfId
usdPPPoESubIfId.description: An integer identifier for the PPPoE subinterface, used in conjunction with the command-line interface. It is provided here for cross-reference purposes only. The value must be unique among subinterfaces configured on the same underlying PPPoE interface. If this object is not configured, or is configured with a value of -1, a nonzero value will be allocated internally and can be retrieved from this object after table entry creation has succeeded. A value of zero for this object is reserved for future use.

usdPPPoESubIfSessionId.name: usdPPPoESubIfSessionId
usdPPPoESubIfSessionId.description: The current sessionId associated with this sub-interface.

usdPPPoESubIfMotm.name: usdPPPoESubIfMotm
usdPPPoESubIfMotm.description: A message to send via a PADM on the sub-interface when the sub-interface transitions to the ifOperStatusUp state. The client may choose to display this message to the user.

usdPPPoESubIfUrl.name: usdPPPoESubIfUrl
usdPPPoESubIfUrl.description: A URL to be sent via a PADM on the sub-interface when the sub-interface transitions to the ifOperStatusUp state. The client may use this URL as the initial web-page for the user.

usdPPPoEGlobalMotm.name: usdPPPoEGlobalMotm
usdPPPoEGlobalMotm.description: A message to send via a PADM to all sub-interface that are currently in ifOperStatusUp state. A client may choose to display this information to the user. Retrieving this object always returns a null string.

usdPPPoEProfileTable.name: usdPPPoEProfileTable
usdPPPoEProfileTable.description: This table contains entries for the PPPoE portion of a profile entry.

usdPPPoEProfileEntry.name: usdPPPoEProfileEntry
usdPPPoEProfileEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of the PPPoE components of a profile entry. Each entry is applied to an interface when the IP interface above the PPPoE sub-interface becomes active.

usdPPPoEProfileIndex.name: usdPPPoEProfileIndex
usdPPPoEProfileIndex.description: This is the index of the profile that the attributes are being set in. The index must exist before creating a row in this table. The index is equivalent to usdProfileIdId in the usdProfileIdTable.

usdPPPoEProfileRowStatus.name: usdPPPoEProfileRowStatus
usdPPPoEProfileRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy The index must exist in the profile manager before this entry can be created. CreateAndGo simply adds a table entry to the PPPoE component. Destroy deletes the entry in the PPPoE component (but not the entry in other components), and removes all PPPoE information relating to this profile.

usdPPPoEProfileMotm.name: usdPPPoEProfileMotm
usdPPPoEProfileMotm.description: A message to send via a PADM on the sub-interface when this profile is applied to the IP interface above this PPPoE sub-interface. A client may choose to display this message to the user.

usdPPPoEProfileUrl.name: usdPPPoEProfileUrl
usdPPPoEProfileUrl.description: A URL to be sent via a PADM on the sub-interface when this profile is applied to the IP interface above this PPPoE sub-interface. The string entered here can have several substitutions applied: %D is replaced with the profile name %d is replaced with the domain name %u is replaced with the user name %U is replaced with the user/domain name together %% is replaced with the % character The resulting string must not be greater than 127 octets long. The client may use this URL as the initial web-page for the user.

usdPPPoEMajorInterfaceCount.name: usdPPPoEMajorInterfaceCount
usdPPPoEMajorInterfaceCount.description: The total number of PPPoE major interfaces configured and created in the system.

usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfAdminUp.name: usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfAdminUp

usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfAdminDown.name: usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfAdminDown

usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfOperUp.name: usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfOperUp

usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfOperDown.name: usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfOperDown

usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfLowerLayerDown.name: usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfLowerLayerDown
usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfLowerLayerDown.description: The total number of PPPoE major interfaces in the system with an operational state of lowerLayerDown(7).

usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfNotPresent.name: usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfNotPresent
usdPPPoESummaryMajorIfNotPresent.description: The total number of PPPoE major interfaces in the system with an operational state of notPresent(6).

usdPPPoESummarySubInterfaceCount.name: usdPPPoESummarySubInterfaceCount
usdPPPoESummarySubInterfaceCount.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces configured in the system.

usdPPPoESummarySubIfAdminUp.name: usdPPPoESummarySubIfAdminUp
usdPPPoESummarySubIfAdminUp.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces in the system that are administratively configured to up(1).

usdPPPoESummarySubIfAdminDown.name: usdPPPoESummarySubIfAdminDown
usdPPPoESummarySubIfAdminDown.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces in the system that are administrateively configued to down(2).

usdPPPoESummarySubIfOperUp.name: usdPPPoESummarySubIfOperUp
usdPPPoESummarySubIfOperUp.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces in the system with an operational state of up(1).

usdPPPoESummarySubIfOperDown.name: usdPPPoESummarySubIfOperDown
usdPPPoESummarySubIfOperDown.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces in the system with an operational state of down(2).

usdPPPoESummarySubIfLowerLayerDown.name: usdPPPoESummarySubIfLowerLayerDown
usdPPPoESummarySubIfLowerLayerDown.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces in the system with an operational state of lowerLayerDown(7).

usdPPPoESummarySubIfNotPresent.name: usdPPPoESummarySubIfNotPresent
usdPPPoESummarySubIfNotPresent.description: The total number of PPPoE subinterfaces in the system with an operational state of notPresent(6).
